How to install docker in ubuntu 


wget -qO- https://get.docker.com/ | sh
apt-get install docker-compose
docker build -t harish:latest1 .
docker images
<docker rmi repository:tag or imageid>

docker pull ubuntu -  build image 
if we have soucr code,then build images from source code by using "docker build" - only image 
"docker run" command used to create containers from docker images 
"docker compose" to build image and create container
docker ps - display running containers info
docker ps -a - all containers information 
docker run -itd <image_name>
docker exec -it <container_name> sh - connecting to container
docker exec -it <container_name> ls /home - executing ls commands without connect to container 
